data.enText: the act of behaving in a particular way, in order to make other people believe sth that is not true

data.chText: 他们的友善态度只不过是装出来的。
到晚会结束时，她已将假装的兴趣抛得一干二净。
data.enText: By the end of the evening she had abandoned all pretence of being interested.

data.chText: 他未敢妄称音乐知识丰富。
data.enText: He made no pretence of great musical knowledge.

data.chText: 她无法继续假装爱他了。
data.enText: She was unable to keep up the pretence that she loved him.
a claim that you have a particular quality or skill

data.chText: 自诩有几分姿色的女人
data.enText: a woman with some pretence to beauty

data.chText: 我不敢自诩为这方面的专家。
data.enText: I make no pretence to being an expert on the subject.

data.chText: 靠欺诈手段；以虚假的借口
data.enText: by pretending to be sth that you are not, in order to gain some advantage for yourself
She was accused of obtaining money under false pretences.

tr: the act of giving a false appearance

example: under the guise of friendship he betrayed them

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 pretense

value.def: A pretence is an action or way of behaving that is intended to make people believe something that is not true.

example.ex: Welland made a pretence of writing a note in his pad...
example.tran: 韦兰假装在便笺薄上做笔记。

example.ex: We have to go along with the pretence that things are getting better...
example.tran: 我们只得一直假装情形在好转。

example.ex: The government abandoned any pretence of reform.
example.tran: 政府不再装模作样地进行改革。

value.def: If you do something under false pretences, you do it when people do not know the truth about you and your intentions.

example.ex: I could not go on living with a man who had married me under false pretences...
example.tran: 我再也不能和一个靠谎言骗我结婚的男人继续生活下去了。

example.ex: Conrad had been imprisoned for a year for gaining money by false pretences.
example.tran: 康拉德因为诈骗钱财已经坐了一年的牢。

value.tran: 以虚假的借口；以欺骗的手段
